          <h2>Apples</h2>
          <div class="xyz">
           <div class="pqr">
            Apples are a rich source of pectin, a soluble fiber.<br>

Pectin bypasses digestion in your small intestine and is then broken down by the friendly bacteria in your colon.<br>

It increases stool volume and is therefore commonly used to resolve constipation and diarrhea. It has also been shown to decrease the risk of intestinal infections, as well as inflammation in the colon.
           
      
         
