           <h2>Beets</h2>
           <div class="xyz">
               <div class="pqr">
                Beetroot, otherwise known as beets, is a good source of fiber.<br>

One cup (136 grams) of beets contains 3.4 grams of fiber. Fiber bypasses digestion and heads to your colon, where it feeds your healthy gut bacteria or adds bulk to your stool — which both improves digestion.<br>

A few popular ways to eat beets include roasted, mixed in a salad, pickled or blended into a smoothie.
          
                
    
