           <h2>Ginger</h2>
           <div class="xyz">
               <div class="pqr">
                Ginger is a traditional ingredient in Eastern medicine that helps improve digestion and prevent nausea. Many pregnant women use it to treat morning sickness .<br>

From a digestion standpoint, this yellowish root has been shown to accelerate gastric emptying.<br>

By moving food from your stomach to your small intestine quicker, ginger reduces your risk of heartburn, nausea and stomach discomfort.
                
